1. Ancient writings may contain biases and inaccuracies due to their romanticized nature.
2. The accuracy of ancient writings is compromised by their subjective and personal perspectives.
3. The romanticized view presented in ancient writings may not reflect the actual social dynamics and structures of Indo-Aryan society.
4. Ancient writings may have been written with the intention of promoting a particular ideology or agenda, rather than providing an objective account.
5. The historical context in which ancient writings were created may have influenced the way they portray Indo-Aryan society.